added.title: Sleep

added.title: Heatblast AW3: The Fast and the Fiery
added.description: A Kineceleran delegation visits Pyros to discuss diplomacy and ends up in a heated game of Fireball, the Pyronites' planetary pastime, now kicked up a notch thanks to their speedster guests.

added.title: Slapback AW3: Population Override
added.description: The Ekoplektoids' amoebic ability to multiply their own cells and subdivide into smaller, denser clones leads to out-of-control overpopulation, forcing them on a space expedition for more space.

added.title: XLR8 AW3: The Slow Age
added.description: After centuries of failing to break their own land-speed records, the Kinecelerans put an end to "The Slow Age" by teaming up with the Arburian Pelarotas.

added.title: Diamondhead AW2: Great Petropian Civil War Part  2
added.description: The Petrosapien Civil War comes to a crucial turning point as the crystalline Petrosapiens make the hard choice to team up with their warring sub-surface cousins, the Subsapiens, to defeat the monstrous Antrosapiens that dwell near Petropia's dark planetary core.

added.title: Shockrock AW2: Fulmanian Conquest
added.description: For the Fulmini, enough is just never enough. Traveling from planet to planet, draining worlds of their energy, this mighty race of conquerors must siphon energy from other planets in order to keep their own tapped-out planet spinning.

added.title: Grey Matter AW2: Lights Out!
added.description: A reliable power supply is vital to the Galvans' around-the-clock research, so when disaster strikes, or more specifically energy-sapping parasites, these brainy beings must have an even more reliable backup plan for keeping the lights on.

added.title: Four Arms AW2: The Warspear
added.description: A look at the perilous lengths to which the Tetramands must go in order to forge their formidable Warspears— the weapons that allow them to survive in such a savage wilderness.

added.title: XLR8 AW2: Speed Round
added.description: The Kinecelerans live life at the fastest pace possible, even when they're letting off steam— hence their supercharged take on what we Earthlings call hockey, where every point is more electrifying than the last!

added.title: Heatblast AW2: Cold Snap
added.description: Join the Pyronites as they ring in the holidays with a special tradition that would make even the most warm-blooded of visitors go crazy from the heat— racing to the top of Mount Helios, an active volcano!

added.title: Wildvine AW2: The Worldtree
added.description: The Verda World Tree gives life to the entire ecosystem surrounding it, but like any organic matter, this magnificent specimen has a life cycle of its own. That's where the Florauna come in, herding wild Mushroars, gigantic pollen beetles, to fertilize the wilting tree in time for a blooming spring.

added.title: Overflow AW2: Sentries of Cascareau
added.description: When the Cascan Pirates aren't plundering the depths of Cascareau for buried treasure, they're depositing their spoils into savings accounts at the Fort Knox of the high seas — a bank built atop an ever-drifting island of pontoon boats, guarded by telepathic Cephalopods, its vaults impenetrable to all but the most loyal customers.

added.title: Cannonbolt AW2: When Mega-Sharks Attack!
added.description: Arburia is well-known across the galaxy for its beach season but this year's interplanetary vacationers won't be catching many waves if the Pelarotas can't rid their waters of an unwanted visitor: the Carcharadon, a billion-toothed beast that makes Jaws look like canned tuna!

added.title: Stinkfly AW2: The Sweet Smell of Survival
added.description: For the Lepidopterrans, putting food on the family table is never as simple as running out to the grocery store. Watch as their elite Sky Soldiers go mandible-to-mandible with fearsome Tongue Beetles in what's sure to be a hunger game for the ages!

added.title: #RemoteUncontrolled
added.description: When they can't agree on a show to watch, Harleen Quinzel and Pam Isley end up in a super battle over the remote.

added.title: #Vegecide
added.description: Jessica Cruz does battle with her own smoothie when Poison Ivy wreaks havoc on a vegan restaurant.

added.title: #BatAndSwitch
added.description: Zee Zatara's attempts to help Barbara Gordon see eye to eye with her father backfire when her magic spell doesn't work as planned.

added.title: #ComicGone
added.description: Barbara Gordon and Harleen Quinzel both covet the same rare comic book, but don't want to let it come between them. Batgirl and Harley Quinn, on the other hand.

added.title: #EqualTights
added.description: Green Lantern (Hal) tries to impress his hero, Superman, with his heroing prowess.

added.title: #StainedFighter
added.description: Kara Danvers needs to stop a villain but her super-girl costume is in the wash!

added.title: A Fury Scorned
added.description: Lashina breaks into Belle Reve and poisons Commissioner Gordon. Batgirl and Hawkgirl must find the antidote before it's too late.

added.title: Ares up There
added.description: When Wonder Woman is home for a holiday, Ares, the god of war, attacks.

added.title: Gorilla Warfare
added.description: The supers must save Gorilla Grodd when his former army comes to "rescue" him from SHH.

added.title: Around Metropolis in 80 Seconds
added.description: Wonder Woman and Supergirl are facing off to see who's fastest, but when they keep tying, they decide to race sans superpowers. Harley hates to be left out and joins the race. As Wonder Woman and Supergirl zoom around Metropolis, they spot a bank robbery in progress and compete to see who can catch the criminals first. While they're distracted, Harley wins the race.

added.title: For Art's Sake
added.description: It's the SHH Student Art Fundraiser and the Double Dare Twins have stolen a masterpiece from the show! It's up to Katana and Supergirl to stop them and recover the painting. But when Supergirl is knocked out by kryptonite and Katana's sword is stolen, Katana must improvise and use her art supplies to defeat the Double Dare Twins.

added.title: Body Electric
added.description: Giganta causes an electric blackout and Batgirl enlists the help of Thunder and Lightning,

added.title: Day of Fun-Ship
added.description: Starfire and Blackfire must protect the zoo from King Shark and realize they have more in common than they thought.

added.title: Dog Day After School
added.description: A Krytptonian is loose in Metropolis! After following the wake of school destruction, Supergirl is reunited with Krypto the Super Dog.

added.title: Seeing Red
added.description: A red Kryptomite, loose at Super Hero High, brings out everyone's mean side.

added.title: Wildside Part 2
added.description: With Lion-Mane subdued, Batgirl, Starfire, and Beast Boy must find all the escaped zoo animals and return them to the zoo. With the help of zoo volunteer, Mari McCabe (Vixen), they return the animals to their proper place at the zoo.

added.title: It's a Superful Life
added.description: The girls want to make this an extra special holiday by brightening the lives of Metropolis citizens.

added.title: Techless Tuesday
added.description: Mrs. Clayface steals all of Batgirl's gadgets in an effort to break her husband out of Arkham.

added.title: Batnapped
added.description: Batgirl is kidnapped by Killer Moth, who wants to make her his partner! Too bad Batgirl already has a partner, Supergirl.

added.title: Surprise
added.description: Harley enlists the help of Katana and Bumblebee in hiding a surprise birthday present for Batgirl in her dorm room. But when they sneak into Batgirl's dorm, they are accosted by Batgirl's booby traps.

added.title: Fight Flub
added.description: Katana and Big Barda try to prove their own fighting style is the best when the Double Dare Twins attack.

added.title: Fresh Ares Part 1
added.description: A peaced out Ares comes to Metropolis to see Wonder Woman, but his peaceful outlook is ruined when Catwoman steals the Amulet of Harmonia.

added.title: Stealth 101 Part 1
added.description: Batgirl and Ivy are partnered for Crazy Quilt's stealth suit design project.

added.title: Spring Prison Break
added.description: Frost reads her "How I Spent Spring Break" essay and we flashback to the tale of how Katana and Frost formed the first "Task Force X" to stop Lashina from breaking the Female Furies out of Belle Reve. During the battle between the SHH Heroes and the Furies, Barda redeems herself and joins the side of the good guys.

added.title: Fresh Ares Part 3
added.description: With Catwoman's help, the supers return the amulet to Ares and save the day.

added.title: New Perry-Spective
added.description: Batgirl, Big Barda, and Lady Shiva set off in the Mobile HQ to wrangle Perry the Parademon. Perry playfully destroys various bits of Metropolis as the supers chase him. The supers manage to catch him and wait in anticipation, thinking Granny Goodness is behind this. However, it seems Perry has been abandoned by his previous owner, and just wants to play. Big Barda decides to keep Perry as her pet.

added.title: Wildside Part 1
added.description: Batgirl, Beast Boy and Starfire are picnicking in the park when Lion-Mane's menagerie of entranced animals attack the park. The heroes must save the citizens and stop Lion-Mane.

added.title: Tales from the Kryptomites Part 2
added.description: The supers must save Metropoils from the army of Kryptomites.

added.title: Tales from the Kryptomites Part 1
added.description: Lena Luthor uses kryptonite remnants from Supergirl's ship to create living Kryptomites.

added.title: Jetsetters
added.description: Wonder Woman is teaching Frost how to fly the Invisible Jet when Killer Moth detects them and begins to attack. Frost takes the ejector Turbo Seat to fight back. However, the jet is damaged by Killer Moth's ship, and the jet begins to plummet. The ship goes into emergency lockdown and Wonder Woman is trapped. She manages to lift the jet from the inside and crash into the bay instead of the city. Frost makes a giant ice cube that allows the jet to float and freezes Killer Moth's plane. With Killer Moth defeated, Supergirl melts the ice around Wonder Woman's jet and Batgirl restores functionality to the jet's tech. Wonder Woman emerges unscathed.

added.title: Fresh Ares Part 2
added.description: As Ares reigns destruction on Metropolis, the supers must recover the amulet.

added.title: Stealth 101 Part 2
added.description: Batgirl and Ivy learn to appreciate each other's style as they fight Killer Moth.

added.title: New Beginnings
added.description: Wonder Woman shows Supergirl around Super Hero High.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Supergirl
added.description: Supergirl is anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: Batgirl vs. Supergirl
added.description: Batgirl and Supergirl face off in a quest for the last piece of superfood cake.

added.title: Quintessential Harley
added.description: When Harley's web videos go viral, she deals with the unexpected consequences of fame.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Harley Quinn
added.description: Harley Quinn is anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: License to Fly
added.description: Batgirl builds her Batjet. But before she can fly, she must pass the Flyer's Exam.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Batgirl
added.description: Batgirl is anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: Doubles Trouble
added.description: Katana chooses Supergirl as her tennis doubles partner, but Supergirl's powers are too much for the game.

added.title: Franken-Ivy
added.description: Ivy creates a new plant pet which grows out-of-control and attacks Metropolis.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Katana
added.description: Katana is anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: The Blunder Games
added.description: As part of the Advanced Survival Skills class, Batgirl is dropped off in a remote island and must make it to the designated meeting spot before sunset. But when her equipment malfunctions, Batgirl must rely on a different set of super skills.

added.title: The Cheetah Who Cried Wolf
added.description: Cheetah attempts to win Hero of the Month through various Save the Day situations.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Frost
added.description: Frost is anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: Dude, Where's My Invisible Jet?
added.description: Wonder Woman loses her invisible jet.

added.title: Hawkgirl's Day Off
added.description: Hawkgirl's friends surprise her with a relaxing day at the spa. But when Hawkgirl takes on Mrs. Clayface in the mud bath, her friends find that fighting crime is Hawkgirl's preferred way of relaxing.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Hawkgirl
added.description: Hawkgirl is anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: The Ultimate Accessory
added.description: Bumblebee must design an accessory for her Weaponomics class. But instead of designing for herself, she finds more inspiration in her friends.

added.title: Ring of Mire
added.description: Star Sapphire loses her violet lantern ring down the drain and must venture into the sewers. Ew ew ew!

added.title: Hero of the Month: Star Sapphire
added.description: Star Sapphire is anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: Riddle of the Heart
added.description: The Riddler stages a series of crimes in order to lure Batgirl to the rose garden where he asks her to the dance.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Cyborg and Starfire
added.description: Cyborg and Starfire are both anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: Roomies Return: Frost's Bite
added.description: When Frost can't get her warmth from any of her normal sources, her grumpiness causes icy havoc around the school.

added.title: The Odd Couple
added.description: Harley and Lady Shiva are paired for a stake out assignment and must capture a villainous named Cheshire.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Lady Shiva
added.description: Lady Shiva is anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: Cold Blooded
added.description: Frost catches a cold and each sneeze and sniffle causes her to freeze everything around her.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Beast Boy
added.description: Beast Boy is anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: Welcome to Super Hero High
added.description: The school's official greeting video hosted by Principal Waller. Principal Waller introduces the school and curriculum to potential new students.

added.title: All About Super Hero High
added.description: Wonder Woman arrives at Super Hero High. Waller introduces Bumblebee as the Ambassador to New Students. Bumblebee gives Wonder Woman the tour of Super Hero High and introduces her to some of the main Supers.

added.title: Roomies
added.description: Wonder Woman meets her new dorm-mate, Harley Quinn. Harley is obsessed with the new girl, but Wonder Woman just wants some peace and quiet so she can study. In the end, Wonder Woman and Harley hit off their unexpected friendship.

added.title: Power Outage
added.description: It's Wonder Woman's first day of Flyer's Ed and her chance to prove to Red Tornado, the instructor, what a great flyer she is. But her lap through the aerial obstacle course is fraught with disaster when Cheetah takes control of Wonder Woman's flight safety belt.

added.title: Crazy Quiltin
added.description: Wonder Woman is introduced to an important rite-of-passage for all new students at the school: creating your own iconic super hero suit. But super suit design is not Wonder Woman's forte. She brings in Katana, Bumblebee, and Harley to help her in this important task, but the results leave something to be desired.

added.title: Fall into Super Hero High
added.description: Harley Quinn reveals she made a tribute video for her friends, which they learn is a montage of them screwing up while using their powers. Their embarrassment is heightened when they learn Harley has accidentally uploaded the video and it's gone viral! Seeing the absurdity and laughing at herself, Wonder Woman breaks the girls' stunned, mortified silence. The laugh catches on. Because of Wonder Woman's leadership, all the girls who were initially embarrassed are able to laugh at themselves.

added.title: Designing Disaster
added.description: Wonder Woman finishes her super suit for Crazy Quilt's class and it's time to try it out. But the suit is a mish-mash of super hero tropes and isn't practical for saving the day. Her attempts to respond to a Save the Day drill end in disaster as her suit trips her up.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Bumblebee
added.description: Principal Waller makes her monthly announcement where she anoints a student as the Hero of the Month. This month, the H.O.M. is Bumblebee. Waller shows a video montage of Bumblebee's exploits including saving her friends plus little comedic beats where Bumblebee changing size causes her to split a seam in her costume.

added.title: Clubbing
added.description: Principal Waller tells Poison Ivy that she needs to join a club in order to fulfill her extracurricular requirements. However, clubs are not introverted Ivy's idea of fun. Hawkgirl and Bumblebee invite Ivy to join the Junior Detective Society. Miss Martian and Starfire give Ivy the pitch for the Model United Planets. Katana and Beast Boy want her for Band Club. But then, the glimmering test tubes of Science Club catch Ivy's eye. Ivy adds her name to the sign-up sheet manned by Frost and Flash. Later, during the first Science Club meeting, Ivy shows off her modified plants, which creates chaos for Star Sapphire. Ivy grins. Clubs are fun!

added.title: Weaponomics
added.description: It's demonstration day in Lucius Fox's Weaponomics class. Catwoman wields her whip. Hawkgirl swings her mace. But when Wonder Woman demonstrates her lasso, a sneaky maneuver from Cheetah causes her to lasso Mr. Fox, who spills his secrets in the lasso's grip. The incident leads to Wonder Woman getting detention!

added.title: Hero of the Month: Poison Ivy
added.description: Principal Waller makes her monthly announcement where she anoints a student as the Hero of the Month. This month, the H.O.M. is Poison Ivy. Waller shows a video montage of Poison Ivy's exploits as Ivy saves the students from the grip of her out-of-control plants.

added.title: Saving the Day
added.description: It's time for Wonder Woman to reveal her new super suit for Crazy Quilt's final grade. Bumblebee, Harley and Ivy watch from the sidelines in support of their friend. Wonder Woman steps onto the catwalk and reveals her new outfit. But before Crazy Quilt announces Wonder Woman's grade, the Save the Day alarm buzzes! Wearing her new costume, Wonder Woman leads Bumble Bee, Harley, and Ivy on a mission to save the day! They must save Mr. Fox who's stuck on top of the Amethyst! The girls save their teacher, but in the process, Wonder Woman discovers that Cheetah was behind this malicious deed. In the grip of Wonder Woman's lasso, Cheetah confesses all her crimes.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Wonder Woman
added.description: Principal Waller makes her monthly announcement where she anoints a student as the Hero of the Month. This month, the H.O.M is Wonder Woman. Waller shows a video montage of Wonder Woman's exploits, which is mix of big heroic moments, and the small beats of friendship, laughter and fun. Wonder Woman's heroism isn't just about superpowers, but also about the amazing, caring person she is.

added.title: Need for Speed
added.description: The Flash is running wild in Metropolis! Lena Luthor has strapped a confusion inducing Blue Kryptomite to his back and now he's running so fast that he's shaking the foundations of Metropolis. It's up to the girls at Super Hero High; Batgirl, Wonder Woman, Supergirl and Bumblebee, to stop The Flash in his tracks and save Metropolis!

added.title: Trading Places
added.description: Lena Luthor has created a power nullifying device and she is threatening to use it on Superhero High! Now, Batgirl and Supergirl will have to trade places to infiltrate Lena's lab and put the power nullifying device out of commission for good.

added.title: Wonder Waitress
added.description: Wonder Woman is used to saving the world from dire threats a couple of times a week but this time she'll face her greatest challenge yet: Waitressing. When Steve Trevor's waitress quits her job mid shift at Capes and Cowls Café it's up to Wonder Woman to step in and save the day!

added.title: Crazed and Confused
added.description: Mad Harriet has stolen Batgirl's Batjet and she's threatening Superhero High with it. Batgirl, Wonder Woman, Supergirl and Harley Quinn have to stop her. But as dangerous as Mad Harriet being on the loose is will Harley Quinn's help be even worse?

added.title: Bodybuilding
added.description: Batgirl, Bumblebee and Cyborg have teamed up for the Creative Heroic Engineering Project at Superhero High. The only problem is they can't agree on anything! When Lena Luthor attacks with her new Rainbow Kryptomites our heroes will have to learn to work together to defeat her.

added.title: Showdown
added.description: The Furies are back and this time they've stolen a very important document from Principal Waller that could have dire ramifications for Superhero High and the World! It's up to Wonder Woman and Katana to take down the Furies and save the day!

added.title: The Cave
added.description: The Bears try to get rid of a bat in their cave.

added.title: Cooking with Ice Bear
added.description: Ice Bear has a Korean-style cooking show and teaches the audience how to cook authentic Korean dishes.

added.title: Frozen Ice
added.description: Grizz and Panda find Ice Bear frozen in a block of ice and attempt to save him.

added.title: Bear Stack
added.description: The Bears travel to the video game store to buy the last copy of a coveted new game. They encounter video game-like obstacles along the way.

added.title: Assembly Required
added.description: The Bears have trouble assembling some recently purchased furniture.

added.title: Panda's Profile Pic
added.description: Panda frets over not having a good photo of himself to send to a girl online. Luckily, his brothers offer their photo editing skills to help.

added.title: Potty Time
added.description: The Baby Bears search for people to adopt them is disrupted by Panda's need to find a bathroom.

added.title: Dreamium
added.description: Panda uses a relaxation app to help him get to sleep. But the the app's different sounds do more harm than good!

added.title: Grizzly: Ultimate Hero Champion
added.description: Grizz records his audition tape for his favorite athletic game show.

added.title: Charlie's Opus
added.description: Charlie plays some abandoned instruments in the woods. But when other animals seem interested in the music, Charlie switches from player to conductor.

added.title: Nom Nom vs. Hamster
added.description: Nom Nom is forced to share the spotlight on his new video with an uncooperative hamster.

added.title: Log Ride
added.description: The Bears become obsessed with taking the perfect "action shot" picture on a log ride at an amusement park. They go on the ride over and over again until they've got the best shot.

added.title: Bear Cleaning
added.description: Ice Bear vacuums the cave and accidentally rips out a patch of Grizz's fur. He tries to fix Grizz's bald spot before he notices.

added.title: Panda's Dream
added.description: Panda gets cut in line while waiting to buy a video game and fantasizes about ways of heroically standing up for himself.

added.title: Goodnight Ice Bear
added.description: Ice Bear tries to fall asleep but the door to his fridge won't close. He tries to come up with a fix for it in any manner possible, no matter how elaborate.

added.title: If Only That Day Was Today Music Video
added.description: Baby bears reminisce written Brad Breeck and Daniel Chong.

added.title: Raincloud Chill Music Video
added.description: Bears just being bears written Brad Breeck and Daniel Chong.

added.title: I Think We Gonna Be Chillin' Music Video
added.description: Chillin' with a burrito written Brad Breeck and Daniel Chong.

added.description: Catch up with this Steven Universe Season 1 recap.

added.title: Season 2 Recap
added.description: Catch up with this Steven Universe Season 2 recap.

added.description: From the Rubies to the Cluster, catch up on all the highlights from Steven Universe Season 3.

added.title: Season 4 Recap
added.description: Catch up with this Steven Universe Season 4 recap.

added.title: Steven Universe Season 5 Catch-Up
added.description: Steven Universe fills you in on everything you need to know about Rose Quartz, the Crystal Gems, and the Diamond Authority before you dive in to new episodes! And there might just be a sneak peek of what's to come.

added.title: Steven Universe Ultimate Catch-Up Trailer
added.description: Take a look back on Steven's journey with this ultimate catch-up trailer!

added.title: Mystery of Rose Quartz
added.description: Recap of previous events before Steven learns more about what happened to Rose Quartz.

added.title: Both of You Music Video
added.description: Music and lyrics by Rebecca Sugar. Additional music by Aivi Tran and Steven Velema. Performed by Zach Callison, Tom Scharpling (speaking) and Deedee Magno Hall (speaking).

added.title: Cooking with Lion

added.title: Driver's Ed
added.description: Space Cabbie is giving a skittish Stargirl a driving lesson through an asteroid belt. "You just need to stop worrying about the things around you and focus on something ahead of you."  Her sense of justice kicks in when she spots Zilius Zox trying to break into a space ATM, and she puts her focus on him, dodging asteroids and Zox's weapons, and putting her driving skills to the test against harrowing distractions!

added.title: The Goddess Must Be Crazy
added.description: Wonder Woman and Supergirl are in a practice mid air combat over Themyscira stadium, and Supergirl loses the round but damages the statue of a horse. Wonder Woman tells her that because of a battle between Superman and Batman, she's taken steps to keep men out of Themyscira. As they continue to train, sorcerer Felix Faust emerges from the broken statue and takes over Supergirl's body. His goal: use her to vanquish Wonder Woman and steal some tempting magical Amazonian artifacts from Themyscira.

added.title: Good Cop, Bat Cop
added.description: Deadshot's been enlisted to put a hit on Batman but with Superman's help they thwart his plan and take him into custody. Stuck in a barren interrogation room, Superman offers to play bad cop for a change but he's such a decent guy that Deadshot just laughs at him. Batman's attempt at playing good cop though seems to make an impression on the villainous creep, and definitely not a good one.

added.title: Beep Beep!
added.description: Lobo has big plans to earn a $100 million bounty on The Flash and "retire on the beach." He uses a distress signal to lure Superman and the Flash to a desert planet (that looks a lot like the setting for Wile E. Coyote's attempts to catch Road Runner). He puts Superman out of commission with a Kryptonite ray gun and cage. Try as Lobo does to catch "the red speedster," the Flash gets around every one of his tricks in a funny salute to the Looney Tunes classics.

added.title: It's a Trap
added.description: Lex Luthor plays a deadly game of "know thine enemy," baiting Superman into a remote hideout in search of a kidnapped woman named Brie Gruyere. The super hero pounds Lex through the ceiling of another building housing the victim, where the "girl" turns out to be a Kryptonite gas spewing robot. As Superman and Lex ponder aloud the predictability of a foe's actions, it looks like Lex, armed with a Kryptonite club, is winning. But he may not know his enemy as well as he thinks.

added.title: Something in the Hair
added.description: Something's odd in the JL Watchtower, Batman has released Poison Ivy from lockup and is giving her a ride home! When Plastic Man protests, one fluff of Ivy's hair releases mind control spores, which he bats away. He follows her into the garage, where she and Batman, on the Batcycle, charge across a bridge of seaweed that Ivy has created toward Metropolis. Plastic Man gives chase, dodging the Batcycle's defensive gadgets. At the docks, there's one last chance for Plastic Man to keep himself alive and break the power of Ivy's spores.

added.title: Up and Atom
added.description: Wonder Woman and Batman are recruiting a reluctant Atom at his lab as a full time Justice Leaguer. "I make things little," he protests. "I'm not, like, a big fighty guy." The pitch is broken up by the explosive intrusion of Etrigan the Demon, who mops the floor with Wonder Woman and Batman when they try to send him back to the dark side. Does "little" guy Atom have enough fight in him? He'll find out once and for all if size matters!

added.title: Plastic Man of Steel
added.description: Lois Lane believes that Clark Kent is Superman, so the Man of Steel enlists Plastic Man to put the doubt back by having him pose as Clark. Lois lures "Clark" to the Daily Planet rooftop and jumps to test him, but she's rescued by, Superman!  But he's hit with red Sun radiation beamed by an armored Lex Luthor, who wants a retraction of Lois's "lies" about him in the paper. The weakened Superman is no match for Luthor in (body armor), so Plastic Man has to stretch to the occasion.

added.title: Chemistry
added.description: HIVE has hit four major tech rooms, and Stargirl keeps an eye out to catch them in the act. But while she's waiting, flirty Firestorm would like nothing more than to impress her by shouting nerdy terms, coached by Prof. Martin Stein ("Keynesian economics, Hegelian dialecticism!") which makes her yawn. As she fends off HIVE's violent attack, Firestorm throws out theory after theory, but it's not helping much. Will he be able to use his own powers and dazzle her at the same time?

added.title: Toymano a Mano
added.description: A hulking robot robs Gotham City National Bank, but it's Cyborg! Toyman has a remote to control his actions. Now Batman is pitted against his own friend, who whips the Batmobile behind him till Batman stops him with a tire "boot." In rocket shoes, Toyman propels himself to the harbor and onto a rubber ducky raft, actually a controlled Plastic Man, who Batman hooks before his ally becomes a reluctant escape airplane. Now Batman needs to call on all of his genius to save his friends.

added.title: Missing the Mark
added.description: When Mark Hamill ("Famous Actor") hails a car for a lift to the Gotham City Conservatory, his driver is none other than The Joker ("Master Villain"), accompanied by Trickster ("2nd Rate Villain"). Mark is lashed to the back seat as the Joker prepares to ransom him to the studios, "who'll pay plenty to get you back!" When the police give chase, the Joker and his "witless wannabee's" argument gets heated, causing the Joker to crash the car into a thicket in the middle of the road, Swamp Thing. Whatever could make the two villains go at each other so?

added.title: Skyjacked
added.description: Under cover of night, Justice One streaks away from the Tower with Poison Ivy and Harley Quinn at the controls! The Batwing interrupts their short lived victory. Struck by one of their missiles, the Batwing starts to plummet. Batman slings a grappling hook onto Justice One and tries to get aboard, only to be launched back into the air on the craft's many separate aircraft, including a submarine. Batman gets aboard to face off with Ivy and Harley, but a smashed guidance system sends the ship plummeting. Batman buckles in. What is he doing?

added.title: Eezy Freezy
added.description: Mr. Freeze has paralyzed Gotham City in ice and helps himself to a jewelry store's inventory. Batman catches him cold, but Mr. Freeze seems to be always two steps ahead of the hero. And Plastic Man's arrival certainly isn't going to help Batman catch Mr. Freeze, who's escaping on a motorcycle. Or will it?

added.title: Special Delivery
added.description: In a bad part of town, Space Cabbie primps waiting for a fare. When Booster Gold and a purple alien bug in labor fight over who gets the cab, Granny Goodness and her minions from Apokolips attack, trying to get Booster Gold. Space Cabbie heads for the hospital as the roof is torn off and Granny Goodness drops in to help with the delivery, with evil intentions for the baby alien. Now Booster Gold has to decide whether to protect the newborn and its mom or try to hitch a ride back to Earth.

added.title: Selfie Help
added.description: Space Cabbie is willing to write off Batman's $38,000 fare in exchange for a selfie with the super hero, to no avail. Inside Justice League headquarters, he spots Booster Gold in a Batman costume, who wants hawk his own Golden Fizz drink brand in the picture then proceeds to photobomb all of Cabbie's shots. When he stumbles into an isolated room where Wonder Woman battles a group of violent attackers, Cabbie has to decide: selfies of the fight, or help an outnumbered super hero!

added.title: Lasso of Lies
added.description: Deadshot 's attempt to assassinate Wonder Woman leads her into a blind alley, where they punch it out as she demands to know who hired him. When she throws the Lasso of Truth around Deadshot, it turns into a limp, pink noodle with the voice of Plastic Man. Adding to the confusion, Booster Gold literally drops in holding the real lasso. An irritated Wonder Woman uses it to draw out some inconvenient truths from Booster Gold. But will she get the information she needs?

added.title: Clown Party
added.description: The Joker and Batman duke it out on a Gotham City rooftop. In their between punch banter, Batman calls the Joker's jokes, "old, but never funny." The villain takes offense and drops a pair of gas bombs, then escapes the explosion with a jet pack, which gets taken down with a Batarang. He falls, spiraling right into a little kid's backyard birthday party. Now, the Joker gets to show off his comic timing with what he's always wanted, a captive audience!

added.title: Super Stakeout
added.description: Green Arrow's stakeout of The Penguin's lair has come up with zero. As if that wasn't bad enough, Plastic Man arrives, in the form of a flying whoopee cushion, to help. Green Arrow gets rid of his loudmouth friend, who returns as a fire hydrant, a rat, and a cat to get closer to the Penguin's HQ. He finds the villain and his thugs, so he delivers himself to their door as a pizza. Inside, it's time to show what he can do against the Penguin and his minions. Now, where's Green Arrow?

added.title: Mint Condition
added.description: Cyborg has good news and bad. Good: he's added lots of new action figures to his collectible toys. Bad: Toyman has turned all the "Bot-Bots," which he's been collecting since childhood, into weapons. In the ensuing battle, a hysterical Cyborg needs to choose whether he's willing to destroy or damage his precious mint condition collectibles, or be a victim of their destruction. Will he stop the battle before they lose all their value, or will he allow Toyman, and his new toy army, to destroy Justice League's headquarters?

added.title: Justice 1, 2, 3, Go!
added.description: Under heavy ground fire, Batman, Wonder Woman, Plastic Man, and Cyborg search for the HIVE headquarters from their aircraft. But HIVE has cloaked its entire operation. The team splits, with Wonder Woman in Justice II and the others in tanks. An excited Plastic Man accidentally deploys the submarine instead, falling into a treetop. Wonder Woman is shot out of the sky and Batman is outmaneuvered and immobilized. It'll take a miracle to get out of HIVE's crosshairs.

added.title: Quality Time
added.description: Wonder Woman explains that "bonding is important" as they unite to fight fires, explosions, and tendrils of monstrous vines that choke off the city. It's all the work of Poison Ivy and her Ivy League. Her gigantic Venus Flytrap of a vine squeezes Batman, Star Sapphire bats away Superman's attempts to catch her, Cheetah puts the Flash out of commission, and Ember makes an explosive entrance to finish him off. Wonder Woman steps in to interrupt the mayhem so the boys can get back in the game. They're all for unity, except for the Dark Knight, but the game they end up with is hardly what anyone expected.

added.title: True Colors
added.description: Superman has Metallo subdued enough to take him back to prison, but when the arch-villain presses a button on his breastplate, it throws Superman in a Kryptonite spotlight, putting him on his knees. Firestorm tries to help, but keeps changing the harmful green Kryptonite into other colors, red, gold, pink and black. Chided by the professor, Firestorm tries hard to remember the formula to neutralize the deadly element.

added.description: In a lesson of survival, Phibby and Prohyas are instructed to create an "Oasis Of Fear" to frighten menacing desert night creatures, but Prohyas scares them away with Magiswords instead.

added.description: A staring contest with Blinky the Flower Boy seems simple enough, too simple, yet when Gateaux makes a spell to make the opponent more formidable, Vambre's Magiswords are needed.

added.description: Professor Cyrus shares that "sick dance moves" can disorient opponents in the Barren Faceland, but when faced with angry frilled running lizards in class Vambre finds that Magiswords help her dance moves.

added.title: Adventure Academy: Sheepy Jungle Shearing
added.description: Prohyas and Bimm need more than just electric clippers to sheer the constantly growing Sheepy Jungle fluff, they need Magiswords!

added.title: Adventure Academy: Snow Decoys
added.description: Ghastly terrors of Transylbiria can be evaded by making snow decoys, but when Morbidia uses magic, her Abominable Snow Decoy must be destroyed by Vambre's Magiswords.

added.title: Adventure Academy: Meatier Milking
added.description: Prohyas and Cattus are chosen to milk a Meatier (a one-horned cow that serves frozen yogurt from its horn), but the pair agitate the beast and Magiswords are required to calm the bull into making desert.

added.title: Adventure Academy: Passe Pirates
added.description: The fashionable pirates of Keelhaul Cove won't mess with you if you garb them in embarrassing garments, but when the lesson goes awry, Vambre needs Magiswords to help save the class from a pirate shakedown.

added.title: Adventure Academy: Barking Broccoli Spider Barkdowns
added.description: To defeat Barking Broccoli Spiders one must beat them at their own game by barking back, but Neddy's fisticuffs approach makes Prohyas' Magisword remedy necessary.

added.title: Adventure Academy: Enchanted Tree Chopping
added.description: Enchanted dust makes a cute little tree spring to life, but Vambre feels bad chopping it down until Witchy Simone casts a spell and it grows to proper Magisword attacking size!

added.title: Adventure Academy: Trollblin Thumb Wrestling
added.description: Professor Cyrus' mechanical Trollblin thumb goes wonky when Bimm attempts the thumb-wresting exercise, so Prohyas uses Magiswords to pin down the rogue machine.

added.title: Adventure Academy: Whack-A-Shark
added.description: Vambre and Phibby Croax are chosen to Whack A Shark in shark tanks, but Vambre decides that Magiswords will do better to defeat them than bops on the shark's schnozzola!

added.title: Adventure Academy: Royal Tower Rescue
added.description: The day's lesson details the four quick steps necessary to rescue royalty from a tower, but when the rabid King Squirrel mauls poor Cattus, its up to Vambre to rescue both with her Magiswords.

added.title: Adventure Academy: Barren Quicksand
added.description: When Prohyas and Familiar do exactly what they're NOT supposed to and sink fast in quicksand, Prohyas resorts to Magiswords to save himself and his fellow kitty student.

added.title: Adventure Academy: Fickle Fishing
added.description: Fishing for the fickle fish of the Fickle Sea is tricky. Vambre and Bimm need special bait to lure them, but when a monster fish attacks Bimm, Vambre comes to the rescue with Magiswords.

added.title: Adventure Academy: Dragonators
added.description: With Gateaux wearing a dragon costume, and Vambre as a dragon-slaying knight, an exercise in dragon slaying takes a dramatic turn when Gateaux's magic turns him into a real dragon!

added.title: Adventure Academy: Ham of Glory
added.description: Phibby Croax wants to fight in the extreme and has no patience to learn the ham-fisted fighting style in the day's lesson called, the Ham Of Glory, so Prohyas breaks out Magiswords to teach Phibby not to be a meathead.

added.title: Adventure Academy: Weather or Naught
added.description: In a lesson on how to control a Weather Gnome, Witchy Simone casts a spell that causes a blizzard and Prohyas must tame the weather with Magiswords.

added.title: Adventure Academy: Sluggernaut
added.description: Professor Cyrus wears a giant slug costume as Vambre and Neddy battle him on the round woody stage, but Vambre avoids a gooey brawl using Magiswords to make her the slug slayer.

added.title: Adventure Academy: Dino Ducking
added.description: Prohyas and Morbidia are chosen to dodge a gauntlet of charging mechanical dinosaurs in today's lesson from Professor C, but Prohyas panics and defeats the mechanized beasts with Magiswords instead.

added.title: Adventure Academy: Adventure Academy 101
added.description: A student introduction gets interrupted by a Monster Attack Dummy come to life and the Warriors take it upon themselves to defeat it with Magiswords.

added.title: To Boulderly Go
added.description: Vambre & Prohyas' quest for the boulder treasure leads them to Grup the Dragon.

added.title: Whose Hyas Is It Anyway?
added.description: The Warriors travel to futuristic Galacton and must figure out a way to get the Confusing Alien Magisword from Nohyas.

added.title: No Robots for Old Men
added.description: Old Man Oldman is back with his secret weapon ‐ Grup taped to the Robopiggeh.

added.title: Attacktus
added.description: The Warriors are sent to the Barren Faceland to water a cactus, which grows into a giant cactus beast that attacks them.

added.title: Zombie Reasonable
added.description: On their quest to find the Zombie Pumpkin Magisword, the Warriors encounter Hoppus, and fight over who saw it first.

added.title: Hands Down
added.description: The Warriors finally get some business doing yard work for Old Man Oldman.

added.title: The Land Before Slime
added.description: Vambre & Prohyas head to the Dinosaur Kingdom to recover a lost baby dinosaur.

added.title: Dolphinominal
added.description: Phil the thief swipes Prohyas' beloved Dolphin Magisword.

added.title: Bark Attack
added.description: A Mysterious Hooded Woman hires Prohyas & Vambre to retrieve the Golden Spectacles from the Tree‐J in the Deepest Darkest Woods.

added.title: Pig Iron
added.description: Vambre & Prohyas compete for the Oinkus Magisword against Super Mighty Robot Piggeh.
